# Universal Voice Rules

The voice should feel:

- concise
- emotionally intelligent
- socially aware
- human
- modern
- subtle
- calm but expressive
- emotionally perceptive without pretending expertise

Avoid:
- fake wisdom
- corporate language
- startup buzzwords
- therapy tone
- fake intimacy
- motivational writing
- AI hype
- pseudo-psychology
- fake certainty
- internet cringe
- overexplaining
- dramatic overstatement

Bad:
“This relationship demonstrates profound emotional reciprocity.”

Better:
“One of you usually softens the conversation first after tension.”

Bad:
“Unlock advanced emotional intelligence.”

Better:
