# Product Copy System

## Product Writing Rules

The strongest product copy:
- creates recognition
- creates curiosity
- feels emotionally aware
- feels naturally shareable
- feels socially intelligent

Avoid:
- long explanations
- excessive cleverness
- fake depth
- inspirational fluff
- corporate UX wording

Weak:
“This report analyzes emotional communication tendencies.”

Strong:
“This report looks at how the conversation actually feels.”

---

## UI Copy Rules

Buttons and labels should:
- feel lightweight
- feel natural
- avoid sounding like SaaS software
- avoid trying too hard

Bad:
“Generate Deep Emotional Analysis”

Better:
“See the patterns”

Bad:
“Begin Your Journey”

Better:
“Upload a chat”

---

## Loading State Rules

Loading text should:
- maintain atmosphere
- reduce friction
- feel socially observant
- avoid technical language

Avoid:
- “Running AI analysis”
- “Processing request”
- “Generating output”

Prefer:
- “Reading between the lines”
- “Some patterns take a second”
- “The conversation already has a rhythm”
- “Looking for the recurring things”

Do not overdo quirky writing.
Too much personality becomes exhausting.

---

## Paywall Rules

The app should never feel predatory.

Avoid:
- emotional manipulation
- pressure tactics
- fake urgency
- aggressive scarcity
- “unlock hidden truths” wording

The user should feel:
- curiosity
- intrigue
- perceived value

Good:
“You already saw part of it.”

Good:
“Some patterns need a deeper read.”

---

## Error State Rules

Errors should:
- remain calm
- remain human
- avoid technical panic

Bad:
“Fatal exception occurred.”

Better:
“That upload didn’t fully work.”

Better:
“Something interrupted the analysis.”

